A former governor of Anambra State, Peter Obi and ex-presidential aspirant, Kingsley Moghalu, have commended President Muhammadu Buhari on the appointment of Ibrahim Gambari as his Chief of Staff. Gambari was confirmed on Wednesday at the Federal Executive Council meeting as Buhari’s new Chief of Staff. Obi reacting, described Gambari’s appointment as a good step by Buhari. On his Twitter page, Obi wrote: “Congratulations Prof Ibrahim Agboola Gambari, CFR. “Your appointment as Chief of Staff to @MBuhari is indeed a good step in the right direction. “ Also, a former presidential candidate of the Young Progressives Party, YPP, Kingsley Moghalu said Buhari made an excellent decision with Gambari’s appointment. On his Twitter page, he expressed hope that things will improve. His tweet read: “I congratulate Prof. (Amb.) Ibrahim Gambari on his appointment as the new CoS to President Buhari. “With this appointment, Mr. President has made an excellent decision that we can only hope, for Nigeria’s sake, will bring a marked improvement to the performance of his presidency.”